{"name":"Elemental Manipulation","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>This power grants basic control over the four traditional elements: air, earth, fire, and water (the elements may vary depending on the setting). The power acts as if it has a d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, or d8 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>Here are some ideas for what each element can do. Each is an action.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Air:</strong> Push someone, blow out a torch, fan a flame, cool someone down (+2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} rolls in oppressive heat).</li>\n<li><strong>Earth:</strong> Move a square foot of earth (half that in stone) each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round}, cover tracks.</li>\n<li><strong>Fire:</strong> Conjure flame about the size of a torch, hurl a small blast of fire at someone (Str damage), spread existing flame (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fire]{Fire}).</li>\n<li><strong>Water:</strong> Conjure a quart of water (not \"inside\" objects or people), purify a gallon of water per casting.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+2):</strong> The volume of air, earth, fire, or water affected is tripled.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Weather (+8): </strong>The caster can summon or dispel storms, bring a cooling rain, scorch the earth with a heatwave, or even bring snow to the hottest climes.\n<p>The caster can bring or disperse rain, snow, sun, and wind in about a five-mile radius. The severity depends on the local environment&mdash;a harsh desert might receive gentle rain while a rain forest gets a driving downpour. The effects take 10 minutes to create and lasts an hour.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A few simple gestures","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"0n04yytSO4RIrteC"}
{"name":"Empathy","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>A successful arcane skill vs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll gives the caster insight into a target's basic emotions. This grants him a +1 bonus (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Performance]{Performance}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Taunt]{Taunt} rolls against the target for the Duration of the power.</p>\n<p><em>Empathy</em> works on animals, adding +1 (+2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Riding]{Riding} or other rolls to interact with the creature.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Charm (+2): </strong>If the target is Uncooperative or Neutral, a successful casting makes him Cooperative, or Friendly with a raise. The spell is instantly broken if the caster or her allies attack the victim or her allies.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character Critically Fails any of the affected skill rolls against the target, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Truth (+2):</strong> The caster knows if the target believes he's telling the truth or not.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration, a warm or sympathetic smile, exchanging a pleasantry","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"186KvMPqqIgc3A34"}
{"name":"Protection","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Protection</em> creates a field of energy or armor around a character, giving him 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the bonus is applied to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} instead (and therefore immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor Piercing (AP)]{Armor Piercing} modifiers).</p>\n<p>Whether the protection is visible or not depends on the Trapping&mdash;this is entirely up to the caster.</p>\n<p><em>Protection</em> stacks with all other armor, natural or worn.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A mystical glow, hardened skin, ethereal armor, a mass of nanites","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"1WVbnkLROAkJhXlH"}
{"name":"Sloth/Speed","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Sloth </em>lessens celerity and coordination while <em>speed </em>increases it. It halves the target&rsquo;s total @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{movement} each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} (round up). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, movement is also an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}. The target automatically attempts to shake off the effects of <em>sloth </em>at the end of each of his next turns by making a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with <em>speed </em>doubles the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{movement} (basic Pace and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running}). With a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} the character also ignores the &minus;2 running penalty.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> <em>Sloth</em> only. For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Quickness (+2):</strong> <em>Speed </em>only. The character's total @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalty each turn is reduced by 2 (she can do two actions at no penalty, or three at &minus;2 each).</li>\n<li><strong>Greater Speed (+2):</strong>&nbsp;<em>Speed&nbsp;</em>only. The recipient&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{running die} isn't rolled&mdash;she gains the maximum result possible.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Sloth</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off <em>sloth's&nbsp;</em>effects is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant (sloth); 5 (speed)","trapping":"Slowing time, blurred motion, a slippery patch of oil or ice","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"23VZeuNqejtjeXDe"}
{"name":"Teleport","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>Teleport allows a character to disappear and instantly reappear up to 12&Prime; (24 yards) distant, or double that with a raise. Teleporting to an unseen location incurs a &minus;2 penalty on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p>Opponents adjacent to a character who teleports away don&rsquo;t get a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Free Attacks]{free attack} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Withdrawing From Melee]{Withdrawing From Melee}).</p>\n<p>If casting teleport on willing subjects, the caster decides where they move to, not the targets.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Teleport (+5):</strong> With concentration, the character can teleport much farther. The caster must concentrate on her destination for at least one round, taking no other actions. This makes her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}; if @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}, the spell fails.\n<p>For one round of concentration, the character can teleport up to 100 miles. For two rounds, she can travel 1000 miles, and with three rounds, she can go anywhere on Eberron. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} transports the recipient to a random location (GM&rsquo;s call) on the same plane of existence.</p>\n<p>If you've physically been there yourself, there is no modifier to your roll. With success you arrive within 2d6 x 10 feet of your target, or on target with a raise.</p>\n<p>If you have a detailed map or have seen it through a power or device, you suffer a &ndash;2 to the roll. With success you arrive within 2d6 x 100 feet, or on target with a raise.</p>\n<p>If you have a crude map or a general notion of the place on a regional or world map, you suffer a &ndash;4. You arrive within 2d10 miles with success, or within 2d6 x 100 feet with a raise.</p>\n<p>In the absence of such information, teleporting is not possible.</p>\n<p>A Critical Failure transports the recipient to a random location (GM&rsquo;s call) on the same plane of existence.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Gate (+5):</strong> Instead of teleporting, the caster opens a temporary portal connecting her current location and the destination. Creatures and objects can travel through this gate from either side for the Duration of the power.</li>\n<li><strong>Teleport Foe (+2):</strong> Foes may be targeted by a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Touch Attack]{Touch attack}. This is an action, which must be the second part of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} if the attack is successful. The foe resists the casting with an opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll against the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} total and is sent up to 12&Prime; away with success and 24&Prime; with a raise. Foes may not be teleported into solid objects.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A cloud of smoke, “phasing” out, change into a bolt of lightning.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"26DOQtfmZju2qkyi"}
{"name":"Detect/Conceal Arcana","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p><em>Detect arcana </em>allows the recipient of the power to see and detect all supernatural persons, objects, or effects in sight for five rounds. This includes <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisible}</em> foes, enchantments on people or items, weird science devices, and so on. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the caster knows the type of enchantment as well.</p>\n<p>When used on a supernatural creature, the caster learns its active powers and arcane abilities. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he knows @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weaknesses} common to that creature type. This doesn&rsquo;t reveal @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weaknesses} of unique individuals, if any. Those must usually be discovered through research or trial and error.</p>\n<p><strong>Invisible Creatures:</strong> <em>Detect arcana </em>also allows a character to ignore up to 4 points of penalties when attacking foes hidden by magical darkness, @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisibility}, or similar abilities (or all penalties with a raise).</p>\n<p><em>Conceal arcana</em> obscures one being or item of Normal Scale or smaller from the detect magic ability for one hour (see Detect Magic on page 169 and the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size Table]{Size Table}). For larger creatures, increase the cost based on the Scale Modifier (+2 PPs for Large, +4 PPs for Huge, or +6 PPs for Gargantuan).</p>\n<p>With a success, attempts to <em>detect arcana</em> on the being or item suffer a &ndash;2 penalty or &ndash;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. If <em>detect arcana</em> fails, the character cannot see through the ruse with this casting and is not aware it is concealed unless presented with obvious evidence of such (for example, the attack of an invisible foe).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one viewer for <em>detect</em>, or item for <em>conceal</em>, for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Alignment Sense (+1):</strong> The caster can sense the presence and exact location of supernatural good or evil within range. Detect arcana activated with Alignment Sense no longer requires line of sight to locate creatures.</li>\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+1/+2):</strong> <em>Conceal&nbsp;</em>only. The power affects everything in a sphere the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} for +1 points, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +2.</li>\n<li><strong>Identify (+1):</strong> The caster can identify a magic item's powers and how they work.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Conceal </em>only. <em>Detection </em>rolls to see through the <em>concealment </em>are made at &minus;2. This stacks with the additional penalty for casting with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5 (detect); one hour (conceal)","trapping":"Waving hands, whispered words.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"2FIrMo5k73po32MD"}
{"name":"Glyph","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>A <em>glyph </em>spell is a way of storing a single spell for activation under a predetermined trigger. <em>Glyphs </em>must be cast simultaneously with a single spell the caster knows that is activated when the <em>glyph</em> is triggered.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Glyphs </em>remain magically charged until activated, which requires a specific trigger. A trigger must contain no more than 10 words, and no more than two clauses. <em>Glyphs </em>aren't intelligent, and although they can recognize their caster they cannot distinguish between other individuals or races. Example triggers are, \"Activate when anyone but me opens that door,\" \"Activate when touched by anyone but me,\" \"Activate when I cry 'Help,'\" and so on.</p>\n<p>A hero may have a maximum number of <em>glyphs </em>cast at anyone time equal to half his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Once triggered, the spell stored in the <em>glyph </em>goes off as normal. It uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{traits} of the caster at the time of the glyph's creation. Once activated, the <em>glyph </em>loses its magic. The caster of a <em>glyph</em>, assuming he is alive, always knows when a <em>glyph </em>has been triggered, regardless of distance, though not which specific <em>glyph</em>.</p>\n<p><em>Glyphs </em>can be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Dispel]{dispelled}, or removed with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Thievery]{Thievery} roll &ndash;2 (or &ndash;4 if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). The caster may erase a <em>glyph </em>he has created simply by touching it and dissolving the magic (an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}). He may also temporarily negate a <em>glyph</em>, thus allowing comrades to pass in safety but not those following him. Negating and reactivating a <em>glyph </em>in this manner takes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action} each and requires the <em>glyph </em>to be touched.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"Special","trapping":"Drawn or inscribed glyph.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"2thsgas15wN3eFA5"}
{"name":"Scrying","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p><em>Scrying</em> allows the caster to secretly spy on a distant target. Preparing the spell takes one uninterrupted minute while the caster focuses on a target item, creature, or location. This makes her Vulnerable and unable to take any other actions. If she's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} during this time, the spell fails.</p>\n<p>If the caster has never seen the target herself, she makes her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll at &minus;2. <em>Scrying</em> on a target in a different plane of existence also imposes a &minus;2 penalty.</p>\n<p><em>Scrying</em> is opposed by the subject's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. If the target wins, he knows he's being spied on. If the caster wins, he can see and hear the target and the area around it but cannot move his perspective. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he can shift perspective and follow the target at a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 24.</p>\n<p>A <em>scrying </em>\"eye\" may be seen with detect arcana (but not detect magic). It may also be dispelled (at &ndash;2 if suspected but not revealed).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Group Sight (+1): </strong>The caster may share her perception with allies within a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} for the power&rsquo;s Duration.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"Images on a reflected surface, glowing eyes, a crystal ball","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"4EuOrGE5zoGilFCC"}
{"name":"Beast Friend","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>This spell allows an individual to speak with and guide the actions of nature&rsquo;s beasts. The cost to cast is equal to the sum of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} (minimum 1 per creature). Controlling five @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dog / Wolf]{wolves} (Size &minus;1) costs 5 points (remember the minimum cost of 1), for example. Controlling a rhino (Size 5) costs 5 points.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the creatures obey simple commands, like a well-trained dog. They attack foes and endanger their lives for their master. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the arcane skill roll means the beasts are more obedient. They won&rsquo;t kill themselves but overcome their natural fears to follow their orders.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarms} can also be controlled. Small Swarms cost 1 point, Medium Swarms cost 2, and Large Swarms cost 3.</p>\n<p><em> Beast friend</em> works only on natural creatures with animal intelligence, not humanoids, and has no effect on conjured, magical, or otherwise &ldquo;unnatural&rdquo; animals.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Bestiarium (+2):</strong> The caster may affect magical and mythical beasts with animal intelligence.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> The base Duration increases to 30 minutes per rank.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through any of the beasts they've befriended.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"The caster concentrates and gestures with his hands.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"5Lv8kVePpRKqFkyr"}
{"name":"Puppet","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p><em>Puppet </em>is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of the character&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. With @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, the victim automatically obeys commands that don&rsquo;t directly harm himself or those he cares about.</p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the target is completely controlled, but gets an automatic @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} to avoid directly arming himself or those he cares about. If the <em>puppet</em>&rsquo;s resistance @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{succeeds}, he doesn&rsquo;t carry out that particular command but doesn&rsquo;t otherwise resist his master. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he breaks the controller&rsquo;s hold and the power ends.</p>\n<p>Commands are general, such as &ldquo;attack that person&rdquo; or &ldquo;open that door.&rdquo; The controller doesn&rsquo;t get to dictate how many @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{actions} the victim uses in a turn, whether or not he uses his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Sweep]{Sweep} Edge, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+2):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 2 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+2): </strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls to resist commands are made at &minus;2. If the caster uses <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Mind Link]{mind link}</em> on the target, she may extend her control of him to any distance, even out of her sight.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Glowing eyes, trance-like state, a swinging pocket watch, voodoo dolls.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"6WdSCcQZg7FQOVE1"}
{"name":"Disguise","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p><em>Disguise </em>allows the target to assume the appearance of another person of the same @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} and shape, including clothing. It does not confer any abilities, however.</p>\n<p>Those who have reason to question the imposter&rsquo;s identity make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll at &minus;2 to see through the <em>disguise </em>(&minus;4 with a raise on the casting roll). This is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong>&nbsp;The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional Power Point each.</li>\n<li><strong>Size (+1):</strong> The recipient may assume the shape of someone up to two @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Sizes} larger or smaller than themselves.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Malleable features, illusionary appearance, hair of new form","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"AxoWs8WR7wHHyycl"}
{"name":"Battle Song","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>This spell, beloved of warlike bards, skalds and dirgesingers, causes the targets to fly into a battle frenzy.</p>\n<p>Every creature within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster, apart from the caster, is granted the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Berserk]{Berserk} Edge for the duration of the spell. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the targets immediately go berserk, as per the Edge. Unwilling recipients are allowed a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} &nbsp;to resist. This spell affects friends and foe alike.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+1):</strong> For +1 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"5","trapping":"Poetry, battle chant.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"BXjhPhx4piUrN3Cb"}
{"name":"Dispel","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Dispel </em>allows a hero to negate enemy powers. It has no effect on permanent enchantments or innate abilities such as a dragon&rsquo;s breath or a banshee&rsquo;s scream. <em>Dispel </em>affects @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Devices]{arcane devices} normally.</p>\n<p><em>Dispel </em>can be used on a power already in effect or to counter an enemy power as it&rsquo;s being used. The latter requires the countering mage to be on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hold]{Hold} and interrupt his foe&rsquo;s action.</p>\n<p>In either case, <em>dispelling </em>an opponent&rsquo;s power is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of arcane skills (with a &minus;2 modifier if the rival&rsquo;s power is of another type such as magic vs. miracles, psionics vs. weird science, etc.).</p>\n<p>If the <em>dispelling </em>character wins, the targeted power ends immediately (or fails if it was countered with the usual results of failure). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the recipient of the <em>dispelled </em>power is also @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Anti-magic Field (+4): </strong>Instead of affecting a power at Range, this modifier creates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster with a Duration of 5. Magic items, effects, and powers have no effect within the field. Summoned creatures that enter the field must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll each round or take a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}. Anti-Magic Field can't be combined with any other modifiers.</li>\n<li><strong>Area Effect (+2/+4/+6): </strong>The effect covers an area: +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} uses a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template}, +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} uses @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium}, or +6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} uses @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large}. The caster makes one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, then each affected target makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll to oppose it. This affects all powers in the target area unless the caster also uses the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Selective (+1)]{Selective} Power Modifier.</li>\n<li><strong>Disenchant (+1):</strong>&nbsp;The caster can target a magical item rather than an individual or a power. This is a standard @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, not an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll}, at &minus;2 penalty (&minus;4 for artifacts, GM&rsquo;s call). If successful, all the item&rsquo;s magical abilities are negated for one round, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n<li><strong>Multiple Powers (+1): </strong>If successful, the caster <em>dispels</em> all the target&rsquo;s currently activated powers.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Waving hands, whispered words","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"BmiqvBJzBorhwGDE"}
