{"name":"Locate","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p>Often it&rsquo;s almost, if not literally, impossible to find something via mundane means. Locate allows the caster to find these hidden things.</p>\n<p>When casters use this power, they choose an object, creature, or location. If the caster has never seen the target, the roll is at &minus;2. A success gives a sense of the general direction and distance of the target. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} also gives an impression of the target (e.g., the creature is asleep, the object is in a strongbox, the secret door is behind a bookshelf).</p>\n<p><strong>Running Water:</strong> On Eberron, running water blocks <em>locate</em> if it&rsquo;s in the path between the caster and the target.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Find the Path (+1):</strong> In addition to the direction and distance to a person, place, or thing, the caster also has a supernatural sense of the best or fastest way to navigate to the target&rsquo;s general area.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"A floating crystal over a map, message in the clouds, a ray of light.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"DvTSc7d7xhxrF2Mn"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000","name":"Seasoned","children":["s7t1gwhTMqHwaPPc","BXjhPhx4piUrN3Cb","wRSuntiUWRvIFJgf","NnDowl5PoJY6TVgD","zS1IHXdyG85Zr2e6","GIfvbgUpwKyzq9hT","AxoWs8WR7wHHyycl","BmiqvBJzBorhwGDE","FPvEfsFu6nM9WR1B","eeTkgu91ZhVGT5qp","LXyQCf9KdqSa91So","R33bU8jAAukI99me","cf12BmLxu6GMPY4q","lHkhPiDJNvbbE22d","W3c7CvvTyFM2pf2p","aeXD2HsOOZgSkfHR","iPDPCyxeXCwV2dea","4EuOrGE5zoGilFCC","XVQUyViTwjWnYlU6","23VZeuNqejtjeXDe","bxN7J6OzYpxJQ8pV","xwN8a3oshjcTDZIw","26DOQtfmZju2qkyi","TzFhrlGGpVBPD8ZZ"],"folderPath":["temp_dbf611102tk"]}},"_id":"EKKPSUbKveOuz72e"}
{"name":"Drain Power Points","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>Powerful mages, priests, and other arcanists can use this ability to drain magical energy from their foes. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} they can even leech the stolen energy for themselves.</p>\n<p>The power is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}, and the caster suffers a &minus;2 penalty to her roll if the target has a different Arcane Background than her own.</p>\n<p>Success drains 1d6 of the rival&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} (if any, and the die doesn&rsquo;t Ace). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the caster adds the points to her own. This may take her above her usual maximum! They last until used, and must be the first spent when casting.</p>\n<p><em>Drain Power Points</em> can also be used on an arcane device (the creator still resists with her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} whether she wields it or not). The device can&rsquo;t lose more @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} than it has.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Power (+2):</strong>&nbsp;The caster drains 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} with success..</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Gusty winds, wings, broomsticks","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"EN387CTM69banCzc"}
{"name":"Resurrection","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>Perhaps the greatest power of all is the ability to bring someone back from the dead. It can restore lost loves, bring solace to the grieving, and topple kingdoms.</p>\n<p>Returning the dead to life requires a reasonably complete corpse no more than a year old. The caster then prays, meditates, chants, or otherwise concentrates on mending the body and pulling the spirit back to it for four hours.</p>\n<p>Once done, the healer makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{casting roll} at &minus;4. If successful, the victim returns to life with three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted}. With a raise, she returns merely @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Resurrection (+10): </strong>The boundaries of life and death no longer matter. A caster can restore the dead to life regardless of how long the target was dead and even without a corpse. To resurrect the dead in this fashion requires a twelve-hour ritual and leaves the caster Exhausted.</li>\n<li><strong>Power (+5):</strong> The hero can raise a spirit dead up to a decade for +5 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"20","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Elaborate ceremonies, rare plants, magical amulets, divine intervention","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6gccwi3q2h","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"ESnYArDbOE1L3PlY"}
{"name":"Boost/Lower Trait","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation/Necromancy}</p>\n<p>This power allows a character to increase or decrease a target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (attribute or skill).</p>\n<p><em>Boosting </em>an ally&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} increases the selected Trait one die type, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, for five rounds.</p>\n<p><em>Lowering </em>an enemy&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of Instant and lowers the selected attribute or skill a die type with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (to a minimum of d4). A victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;Success improves the effect one die type, and a raise removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p>Additional castings don&rsquo;t stack on a single @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Trait} (take the highest), but may affect different Traits.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Boost/Lower Trait (+2):&nbsp;</strong> With success, the selected @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} gains a free reroll once per round, or once per action with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. For <em>lower Trait</em> the target applies a &minus;2 penalty to the affected Trait&rsquo;s rolls.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> <em>Lower Trait</em> only. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll to shake off the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5 (boost); Instant (lower)","trapping":"Physical change, glowing aura, potions","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"EhYYxmBr18igoVzj"}
{"name":"Accelerate Healing","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>The power accelerates the target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing} &nbsp;rate. With a successful casting the target may make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{natural healing} roll once every 24 hour period, with a +2 bonus if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. With a success, the target also gains a +2 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} rolls for resisting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease} during the same time, and a +4 bonus with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The target may only be affected by one casting of accelerate healing at a time.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"24 hours","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EjkmZGPHuQIQbHrQ"}
{"name":"Divination","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p><em>Divination </em>allows the caster to contact otherworldly beings to gain information.</p>\n<p>Preparing the spell takes one uninterrupted minute of prayer, coaxing or otherwise communing with a spirit or deity. Once that&rsquo;s done, the caster makes her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll. Success means the entity answers the character&rsquo;s questions to the best of its ability. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} means the spirit is more helpful, knowledgeable, or direct than usual (whether it wants to be or not).</p>\n<p>Answers are typically vague or symbolic rather than direct&mdash;they provide clues and guidance rather than spoilers that ruin a mystery or adventure.</p>\n<p>The type of entity contacted determines how it communicates. Spirits in the netherworld tend to know only those things pertinent to their life and death&mdash;and they may not even know the identity of their killer if the person was masked or unseen.</p>\n<p>Likewise, nature spirits know only about their local environs, demons know only about the affairs they&rsquo;re directly involved in, and so on. The Game Master must decide what the entity knows based on its background, origin, and personality.</p>\n<p>Once a spirit has been conversed with it may not be contacted again for 24 hours. The Game Master may extend this to a community of spirits in a single place, such as water spirits in a babbling brook or nameless spirits in a mass grave.</p>\n<p><strong>Sacred Ground:</strong> Contacting a spirit on ground sacred to it (a deep forest for fey creatures, a temple for deities, a volcano for fire elementals or infernals, etc.) adds +2 to the roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+3):</strong> This modifier works only on ground sacred to the entity the caster is attempting to contact&mdash;a deep forest for fey creatures, a temple for deities, a volcano for fire elementals or infernals, etc. The being may even manifest or appear in some form with a raise.\n<p>The entity not only answer the petitioner's questions but also offers unsolicited advice. Exactly what and how it's delivered depends on the entity. Woodland creatures may warn the caster about a dangerous area of the forest. A demon might gloat that a greater threat lies ahead, accidentally tipping some other entity's hand in a later encounter.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"A brief conversation of about five minutes","trapping":"Seances, prayers, demonic interrogation.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"FPvEfsFu6nM9WR1B"}
{"name":"Secret Writing","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p><em>Secret writing</em> requires ten minutes to cast and disguises the contents of a page, scroll, book or other suitable writing material, making it appear however the caster wishes. The caster must specify a command word when the spell is cast. Speaking the command word can reveal the true contents of the page or hide it again. Speaking the command word twice in rapid succession removes the spell completely. <em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</em> removes the effects of the spell and reveals the original contents of the page.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Suggestion (+3): </strong>The caster can designate specific individuals who can read it automatically. To everyone else it appears as described above, but with an added effect of a non-harmful suggestion such as \"This scroll never existed.\" The suggestion must be defined when the power is activated. When the suggestion is triggered, the unauthorized reader must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll originally made to activate the power.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","trapping":"Chanting while writing, enchanted paper, magically transcribed spoken words.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"GBtT6ip6WqG0AIHS"}
{"name":"Damage Field","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Damage field</em> creates a dangerous aura around the recipient that harms foes foolish enough to get too close.</p>\n<p>At the end of the affected character&rsquo;s turn, all adjacent beings (including allies!) automatically take 2d4 damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2):</strong> The caster may extend the <em>damage field</em> into a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} centered on herself, the caster is immune to her own damage field.</li>\n<li><strong>Damage (+2):</strong> The damage field causes 2d6 damage.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Damage Field (+4):</strong> The <em>damage field</em> causes 3d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mobile (+2):</strong> Mobile works only with the Area of Effect modifier. It allows the caster to detach the <em>damage field</em> from himself and move it up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} die type each round as a limited free action.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"4","damage":"2d4","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Fiery aura, spikes, electrical field","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"GIfvbgUpwKyzq9hT"}
{"name":"Summon Beast","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>Animals have long been associated with wizards, whether it be the familiars of witches or the fetish beasts of shamans. <em>Summon Beast</em> allows a user to summon mundane animals.</p>\n<p>A character may learn this spell while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Novice}, but cannot summon any larger creatures until he attains the appropriate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}. It materializes anywhere in Range, and with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, it&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Resilient]{Resilient} as well.</p>\n<p>The beast acts on its creator's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card} and follows her basic commands to the best of its ability.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Summon Beast</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Servant</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Novice</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>1 small animal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seasoned</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>1 medium animal or swarm of rats, birds, insects, or other vermin, or 2 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Veteran</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>1 large, 2 medium or swarms, or 4 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heroic</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>1 huge, 2 large, 4 medium or swarms, or 6 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Legendary</td>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>2 huge, 4 large, 6 medium or swarms, or 8 small animals</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Small creatures have a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} less than zero. Medium creatures are Size +0 to Size +3. Large covers Size +4 to +7, and Huge is +8 or larger. Swarms share a similar set of statistics and fill a Medium Burst Template.</p>\n<p>The beast is under the total control of the summoner for the Duration of the spell.</p>\n<p>Animals can only be summoned in their natural terrain. So while a wizard may be able to summon a swarm of rats in Sharn, only on the open plains can he call a lion to his side.</p>\n<p>Summoned creatures appear from the nearest appropriate terrain. For instance, rats swarm out of sewers, a lion emerges from jungle or grass on the savannah, and a swarm of birds descends from the clouds or erupts from the trees. If in doubt, assume the beasts \"appear\" 1d10 x 2 yards away from the caster. When the Duration expires, the animal leaves of its own accord.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><strong><em>Source: Lankhmar, City of Thieves</em></strong></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong>&nbsp;<em>Summon beast's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><strong>Increased Trait (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong>&nbsp;The caster can communicate and sense through the beast.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Animal bones or feathers of appropriate sort, glyphs, chanting.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"IAzG7UZk8u2hPGa0"}
{"name":"Fly","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Fly </em>allows a character to soar at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12&Prime;, or twice that with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (he may not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Run}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+2):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 2 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li><strong>Swift Flight (+5): </strong>The base flying Pace increases to 24 (60 MPH), or 48 (120 MPH) with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gusty winds, wings, broomsticks","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"IuNO91WheiTrTNNs"}
{"name":"Light/Darkness","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Light </em>creates bright @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. With a raise, the light can be focused into a 5&Prime; (10 yard) beam as well.</p>\n<p><em>Darkness </em>blocks @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination}&nbsp;in an area the size of a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}, making the area Dark, or Pitch Darkness with a raise (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}).</p>\n<p>If <em>light </em>and <em>darkness </em>overlap, they create a patch of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Dim light} (&minus;2).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area Effect (+2): </strong>The <em>light</em> expands to the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} in radius, with a Range of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2. The light is sunlight and has the same effect on certain creatures (such as vampires) as natural sunlight.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>True Darkness (+2):</strong> The <em>darkness</em> blocks @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Infravision]{Infravision}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Low Light Vision]{Low Light Vision}, and @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Darkvision]{Darkvision}. It has no effect on magical sight such as <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect arcana}</em>.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round} after casting, or attach it to an inanimate object when first cast.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Illusionary torch, sunlight, darkness, thick fogs","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"Kx5SY5aFVIIHS6lr"}
{"name":"Fortune's Favored","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p>Some heroes are born with a manifest destiny; others need a hand in avoiding an early fate.</p>\n<p>With a successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, a target of this spell that spends a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny} and fails the reroll, may immediately make another reroll without having to spend an additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny}. Only one free roll per @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny} is allowed. If the second roll fails, the hero must spend another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{benny} to reroll again.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Victim glows briefly, catches glimpses of future events, sharing of lucky trinket.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"LXyQCf9KdqSa91So"}
{"name":"Environmental Protection","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>Adventurers sometimes travel beneath the waves, through planes of fire, or other hazardous environments. This power protects them from crushing depths, scathing heat, intense cold, and even radiation.</p>\n<p>Environmental protection allows the target to breathe, speak, and move at his normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} in an otherwise fatal environment. It protects him from intense heat, cold, radiation, pressure, and lack of oxygen.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} increases the Duration to eight hours.</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Enviromental Resistance (+1):</strong> The power now offers environmental resistance, reducing damage from one energy source (fire, cold, electricity, etc.) by 4 (6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"A mark on the forehead, potions, gills.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"MP93zu8gzezwJ5ZY"}
{"name":"Relief","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Relief</em> allows the caster to recover from a negative condition or the effects of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}.</p>\n<p><strong>Recover: </strong>The caster removes one of the following negative conditions: @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted}, or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable}. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll removes two conditions. If affecting more than one target (via the Additional Recipients modifier), the caster may choose which condition(s) to remove for each ally.</p>\n<p><em>Relief</em> can&rsquo;t remove negative conditions caused by ongoing effects (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound or Entangled}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}, etc.) unless the source of the effect is removed.</p>\n<p><strong>Numb: </strong>Reduces the recipient&rsquo;s total penalties from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} by one with success, or two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. An Exhausted (&minus;2) hero with three @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} (&minus;3), for example, reduces her total &minus;5 penalty to &minus;4 with success, and &minus;3 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>This effect lasts one hour. It doesn&rsquo;t actually remove the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} or the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, it just allows the recipient to ignore the penalties. If the target would be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, she&rsquo;s still @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}&nbsp;as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Restoration (+3): </strong>The caster can restore one die type from an energy draining effect with a success, two with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n<li><strong>Stunned (+1): </strong>If using the Recover option, the caster may also affect the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned} condition. This completely removes the effects of being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant/One Hour","trapping":"Prayer, tonics","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"N8XeV4c5yswUpgqE"}
{"name":"Champion of Faith","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>Champion of Faith allows the caster to grant divine favor. For the duration of the spell, the recipient gains the benefits of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Champion]{Champion} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Holy/Unholy Warrior]{Holy/Unholy Warrior} Edge, chosen at the time of casting. Both edges can be taken on a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Holy Aura","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"NnDowl5PoJY6TVgD"}
{"name":"Entangle","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Entangle </em>allows the caster to restrain a target with ice, bands of energy, or other vine-like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings} (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 8). If successful, the target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Entangled}. With a raise, he&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound}.</p>\n<p>Victims may break free on their turn as detailed under @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bound and Entangled]{Bound and Entangled}.</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} or use the Stream Template.</li>\n<li><strong>Damage (+2): </strong>Entangled targets take 2d4 damage at the end of their turn.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Deadly (+4): </strong>Entangled targets take 2d6 damage at the end of their turn.</li>\n<li><strong>Tough (+1):</strong> The <em>entangling</em> material is particularly resilient. Rolls to break free are made at &minus;2 and it's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} increases to 10.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Glue bomb, vines, handcuffs, webs.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"QcASLy2dUYvjsbWe"}
{"name":"Gift of Battle","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Gift of battle&nbsp;</em>grants the target tactical insight and leadership qualities.</p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, the recipient gains the benefits of a single Leadership @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge} chosen by the caster. The caster (not the recipient) must have the same @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} or higher as the Edge&rsquo;s Requirements.</p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the recipient gains two Leadership Edges. He need not meet any requirements except those of other Edges. For instance, the hero cannot gain @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Fervor]{Fervor} unless he scores a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} and takes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Command]{Command} first, or already has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Command]{Command} Edge.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+4):</strong> The recipient gains two (or three with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) Leadership Edges at once.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"4","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gestures, prayer, whispered words, concentration","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"R33bU8jAAukI99me"}
{"name":"Healing","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Healing </em>removes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} less than an hour old. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success} removes one Wound, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes two. The power may be cast additional times to remove additional Wounds within that hour and as long as the healer has enough @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</p>\n<p>For @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}, the GM must first determine if the ally is still alive (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Healing]{Aftermath}). If so, a successful arcane skill roll returns the ally to action (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} if it matters).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Healing (+10):</strong> <em>Greater healing</em> can restore any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, including those more than an hour old.</li>\n<li><strong>Crippling Injuries (+20):</strong> The power can heal a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Injury Table]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{fails}, this caster cannot <em>heal </em>that particular injury (but somoene else may try). If successful, the subject is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Exhausted} for 24 hours.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mass Healing (+2/+3):</strong> For a +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, healing affects all allies within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template} centered on the caster (or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Large Blast Template} for +3).</li>\n<li><strong>Neutralize Poison or Disease (+1):</strong> A successful <em>healing&nbsp;</em>roll negates any @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}. If the poison or disease has a bonus or penalty associated with it, the modifier applies to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll as well.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Laying on hands, touching the victim with a holy symbol, prayer","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"Rhx1RSgjLFbPLGCk"}
{"name":"Warrior's Gift","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, the recipient gains the benefits of a single Combat @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edge} chosen by the caster. The caster (not the recipient) must have the same @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank} or higher as the Edge&rsquo;s Requirements. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the recipient gains the Improved version of the Edge (if there is one, and even if he doesn&rsquo;t meet the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Rank Requirement}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+4):</strong> The recipient gains two Combat Edges at once.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"4","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gestures, prayer, whispered words, concentration","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"TzFhrlGGpVBPD8ZZ"}
{"name":"Darksight","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Darksight </em>allows a hero to see in the dark. With success, he ignores up to 4 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination penalties}. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, he ignores up to six points and can see in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{pitch darkness}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Darksight&nbsp;(+2): </strong> The recipient&rsquo;s senses extend so far into the infrared and ultraviolet spectrums that he ignores all @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{illumination} penalties and 4 points of penalties from @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Invisibility]{invisible} creatures.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Glowing eyes, dilated pupils, sonic sight","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"U3BVlwtKUGAFEEuw"}
{"name":"Zombie","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p><em>Zombie </em>grants animation and basic intelligence to the remains of a once-living being. The summoned horror is obedient but literal-minded in its duties. It isn&rsquo;t telepathic, and must be controlled by voice.</p>\n<p>The being has the physical skills it had in life, but its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}, and related @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills} are reset to d4. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{casting roll} increases any one of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Traits} by one die type (caster&rsquo;s choice).</p>\n<p>Corpses aren&rsquo;t summoned by this ability, so there must actually be a supply of bodies in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} (GM&rsquo;s call).</p>\n<p>An undead @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} by damage can&rsquo;t be raised with this power again.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Zombies (+1):</strong> A larger horde can be raised in a single casting by paying an additional 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;for each extra <em>zombie</em> raised.</li>\n<li><strong>Armed (+1 per Zombie):</strong> The dead rise with a rusting weapon common to their setting and environment. Choose one:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hand Weapon:</strong> Str+d6</li>\n<li><strong>Ranged Weapon:</strong> Range 12/24/48, Dmg 2d6</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Armor (+1 per Zombie):</strong> The horrors crawl from their grave wearing 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Armor]{Armor}. This might be old chain mail, rusting plate, rotting bulletproof vests, etc.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1/+3</strong>): The caster can communicate and sense through one of the undead he&rsquo;s conjured. If it&rsquo;s destroyed, he may jump to any of the others currently under his control. For 3 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, Mind Rider affects all the zombies created in this summoning.</li>\n<li><strong>Permanent (0):</strong> The zombie is given unlife until @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated} by Wounds. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} used to raise it are &ldquo;invested&rdquo; and unavailable until it&rsquo;s destroyed. The necromancer may terminate his creations&rsquo; unlife at any time, regardless of sight, distance, or other factors. His @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;then begin recharging normally.\n<p>Permanent zombies remain animated even if their creator is slain!</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Skeletal (+1 per Zombie):</strong> The corpse sloughs off the anchor of dead flesh and rises as a skeleton. This increases its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting}, and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} dice by one die type each.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Zombie Creatures</strong></h3>\n<p>Animals and other creatures can also be raised with this foul ability! The cost is 2 for a creature of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} &minus;1 or &minus;2, 3 for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} 0, and 1 for a Small @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Swarm]{Swarm}, 2 for a Medium Swarm, or 3 for a Large Swarm.</p>\n<p>Larger creatures cost 3 + @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} in Power Points. For example, an undead grizzly (Size 2) costs 5 Power Points to raise.</p>\n<p>Magical or supernatural @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bestiary]{Special Abilities} aren&rsquo;t conferred to the undead form, but those inherent to the creature are, such as @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Frenzy]{Improved Frenzy}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Reach]{Reach}, a swarm&rsquo;s attack, etc.</p>\n<p>Additional zombie creatures cost half their base cost if raised at once, instead of the +1 listed for <strong>Additional Zombies</strong> (round up, minimum of 1).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<hr />\n<h3><strong>Zombie</strong></h3>\n<p>These walking dead are typical groaning fiends looking for fresh meat.</p>\n<p><strong>Attributes:</strong> Agility d6, Smarts d4, Spirit d4, Strength d6, Vigor d6</p>\n<p><strong>Skills:</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d6</p>\n<p><strong>Pace:</strong> 4; <strong>Parry:</strong> 5; <strong>Toughness:</strong> 7</p>\n<p><strong>Edges:</strong> &mdash;</p>\n<p><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Bite/Claws:</strong> Str.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}:</strong> Zombies are immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Undead)]{Undead}:</strong> +2 Toughness; +2 to recover from being Shaken; no additional damage from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots}; ignores 1 point of Wound penalties; doesn&rsquo;t breathe; immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison}.</li>\n<li><strong>Weakness (Head):</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Called Shots]{Called Shots} to a zombie&rsquo;s head do the usual +4 damage.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Carving symbols on corpses, throwing bones, graveyards, \"leather\" books","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"U4QHFRMqJmb1PrIq"}
{"name":"Fear","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>This power causes overwhelming dread and horror. The target makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{Fear} roll. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras} who fail are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-tables.Fear Table]{Panicked} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Cards} roll on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table}. If the power is cast with a raise, the Fear roll is at &minus;2 and Wild Cards add +2 to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-macros.Fear Table]{Fear Table} results.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Fear (+2): </strong>Fear rolls are made at&minus;2, or &minus;4 if cast with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Gestures, eldritch energy, cold chills","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"VlqgMMNL8lLWAial"}
{"name":"Lock/Unlock","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>Whether guarding valuables or thwarting pursuers, <em>lock </em>allows the caster to seal a door, treasure chest, or other object with a lock. Attempts to pick or smash the lock suffer a &minus;2 penalty, &minus;4 if the caster got a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the casting roll. Also, the locked object gains +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Toughness}, +4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The wizard may open his own locks normally. Opening the <em>lock</em> by any means automatically ends the spell.</p>\n<p><em>Unlock </em>opens any mundane lock, though if the lock is particularly complex, the GM may assign penalties to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll. A door sealed with <em>lock </em>gives a &minus;2 or &minus;4 penalty to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} rolls to cast this spell.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Strong (+2): </strong>For an additional 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the strength of the spell is increased. The <em>lock </em>is subject to a &minus;4 (&minus;6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise})&nbsp;modifier to break or open the object, and an <em>unlock </em>recieves +2 to the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Special (lock); Instant (Unlock)","trapping":"Whispered words, scattering dust on a door, aura around lock, tapping a lock three times.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"W3c7CvvTyFM2pf2p"}
{"name":"Summon Ally","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>This power allows the character to summon a magical servant from nothing. The ally typically takes the form of a basic humanoid of the appropriate Size but can appear differently based on the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings}. It materializes anywhere in Range, and with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, it&rsquo;s @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Resilient]{Resilient} as well.</p>\n<p>The ally acts on its creator&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Action Cards (Initiative)]{Action Card}&nbsp;and follows her commands to the best of its ability. It has no personality, creativity, or emotions. When the power ends or the ally is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, it fades into nothingness, leaving no trace behind.</p>\n<p>The type of servant that can be summoned depends on the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}. With the GM&rsquo;s approval, the player may swap abilities. If a hero wants an attendant in the form of a wolf, for example, the caster might exchange the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} skill for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Survival]{Survival} so that the &ldquo;animal&rdquo; can track its foes.</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Summon Ally</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Servant</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Novice</td>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>Attendant</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seasoned</td>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>Bodyguard</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Veteran</td>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>Mirror Self*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heroic</td>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Sentinel</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*<em>Mirror Self incurs a&nbsp;</em><em>&minus;1 </em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Casting Modifier}<em>&nbsp;per </em><em>Rank above Veteran to a maximum of&nbsp;</em><em>&minus;6&nbsp;at Legendary</em></p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Allies (Varies):&nbsp;</strong> Additional allies of the same type may be summoned at the same time for half the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} cost of the original summons (total cost including modifiers, rounded up).</li>\n<li><strong>Bite/Claw (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The ally can bite or claw at Str+d6.</li>\n<li><strong>Combat Edge (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The ally has a Combat Edge (it must meet the Requirements as usual). You may take this modifier up to three times per ally.</li>\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong>&nbsp;<em>Summon ally's&nbsp;</em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><strong>Flight (+2):</strong> The ally can fly at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} 12</li>\n<li><strong>Increased Trait (+1):&nbsp;</strong> The caster can increase a Trait one die type for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}. She may do this for as many Traits as she likes, but only once per Trait.</li>\n<li><strong>Mind Rider (+1):</strong> The caster can communicate and sense through the ally.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\n<h2>STATBLOCKS</h2>\n<p><strong>Attendant</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Attributes: </strong>Agility d4, Smarts d4, Spirit d4, Strength d4, Vigor d4<br /><strong>Skills:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d6<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>4; <strong>Parry: </strong>4; <strong>Toughness: </strong>4<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Claw: </strong>Str+d4.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct}: </strong>+2 to recover from being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}; ignore 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound penalties}; doesn&rsquo;t breathe, immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Poison]{poison} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Disease]{disease}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Bodyguard</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Attributes: </strong>Agility d6, Smarts d4, Spirit d6, Strength d6, Vigor d6<br /><strong>Skills:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting} d4, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} d4<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>6; <strong>Parry: </strong>5; <strong>Toughness: </strong>7 (2)<br /><strong>Edges: </strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.First Strike]{First Strike}<br /><strong>Gear: </strong>Melee attack (Str+d6).<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Armor +2: </strong>Hardened skin.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct}:</strong> </strong>See Attendant.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Mirror Self<br /></strong>The ally is a clone of the caster except: it&rsquo;s an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Extras}; it has the same number of current @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} as the caster after subtracting for this casting; it cannot use the <em>summon ally </em>power; its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills} (but not @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{attributes}) are one die type less (minimum d4) than the original; it has identical mundane equipment (no magical qualities, disappears when the power expires); has the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless} abilities.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Sentinel<br />Attributes: </strong>Agility d6, Smarts d6, Spirit d8, Strength d12+2, Vigor d10<br /><strong>Skills:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} d6, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Fighting]{Fighting} d10, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} d10, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} d8<br /><strong>Pace: </strong>6; <strong>Parry: </strong>7; <strong>Toughness: </strong>13 (4)<br /><strong>Edges: </strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Improved Sweep]{Sweep (Improved)}.<br /><strong>Gear: </strong>Melee attack (Str+d8).<br /><strong>Special Abilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Armor +4: </strong>Stone skin.</li>\n<li><strong><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Construct)]{Construct}:</strong> </strong>See Attendant.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Special Ability (Fearless)]{Fearless}: </strong>Immune to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fear]{fear} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation}.</li>\n<li><strong>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} 2: </strong>Sentinels are 8' tall and very dense.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Clay figure that grows into a servant, a tattoo that comes to life.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"WjCcuPrR80nMaQHh"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000","name":"Veteran","children":["EjkmZGPHuQIQbHrQ","XsJmNpCa89ECQaRB","owxSMTWZDKq8NWq5","EN387CTM69banCzc","IuNO91WheiTrTNNs","2thsgas15wN3eFA5","ciPkBrXIbIrQfGRQ","ut0XJvwWRwyj5kPL","uDyxykyoTcArW9Pj","crwEHbV2pS1SLTpG","6WdSCcQZg7FQOVE1","U4QHFRMqJmb1PrIq"],"folderPath":["temp_dbf611102tk"]}},"_id":"X7acVrGEdPjKcTJp"}
{"name":"Sentry","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p>Getting a good night's sleep in the middle of orc country is easier said than done. Sentry duty is tiring and lonely, and a single sentry nodding off can spell disaster. <em>Sentry </em>provides additional security for the wary traveler. It can also be used to safeguard valuables.</p>\n<p>The first version of this spell creates a ghostly sentry who watches over the camp but cannot move further away from the caster than the caster's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} x 2 in game inches. The sentry has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} of d8, or d10 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, is always alert, and suffers no penalties for bad lighting. Despite being visible as a ghostly form, the <em>sentry </em>is not a physical manifestation and cannot be harmed, though it can be dispelled .</p>\n<p>The <em>sentry </em>may be given instructions on when to sound the alarm but it is not an intelligent, reasoning being. Instructions may contain no more than 10 words and must be clearly defined. For the purposes of identifying potential threats, the sentry has the same knowledge of monsters and hazards as the caster.</p>\n<p>The second variant protects a single object touched by the caster when he invokes the spell. During the casting, the spellcaster may name a number of individuals equal to half his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type who can safely touch the object. Anyone else touching it immediately activates the spell, which alerts the caster to the tampering.</p>\n<p>The spell automatically expires at sunset or sunrise, whichever occurs first, and the caster may even sleep while the spell is active. It counts as Maintained.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts x 2","duration":"Special","trapping":"Circle of chalk, powder, or blood, mystic rune, staff thrust into ground.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"XVQUyViTwjWnYlU6"}
{"name":"Banish","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Banish </em>sends entities from immaterial planes back to their native dimensions. This includes ghosts, demons, elementals, and similar beings (at the GM&rsquo;s discretion).</p>\n<p><em>Banishing </em>a being is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of the caster&rsquo;s arcane skill versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}, and each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} causes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}.</p>\n<p>If this @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitates} the target it returns to its native plane of existence. <em>Banished </em>entities may return when the Game Master feels it&rsquo;s appropriate, such as the next full moon, when summoned again, or even a few rounds later if it&rsquo;s a particularly powerful creature under the right conditions or in a location of power.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Area of Effect (+1/+2/+3):</strong> For +1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template}. For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Holy items, arcane symbols, handful of salt","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"XsJmNpCa89ECQaRB"}
{"name":"Mind Reading","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p><em>Mind reading </em>is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} versus the target&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} allows the character to gain one truthful answer from the subject. The target is aware of the mental intrusion unless the mind reader gets a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The GM may apply @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{modifiers} based on the subject&rsquo;s mental @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances} or current state of mind.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mind Walk (+2): </strong>The caster has greater access to the target&rsquo;s mind and memories, unlocking an entire scene or chain of related memories (GM&rsquo;s call).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Psionic invasion, soulsight","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"XxBAE0GT8ip6jTil"}
{"name":"Stun","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Stun </em>shocks a target with concussive force, sound, light, magical energy, or the like.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful} casting means the victim must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll (at &minus;2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll) or be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{Stunned}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bolts of energy, stun bombs, sonic booms, burst of blinding light","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"YkXPTQQaMsyPyB0N"}
{"name":"Arcane Protection","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} with arcane protection means hostile powers suffer a &minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}) to affect this character.</p>\n<p>If the power causes harm, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{damage} is also reduced a like amount. Arcane Protection stacks with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-edges.Arcane Resistance]{Arcane Resistance} should the recipient have both!</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Arcane Protection (+2):&nbsp;</strong> Hostile powers suffer a &minus;4 penalty (&minus;6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Concentration, a dull glow around the protected character, a fetish","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"Z8kTiPIDTLHvXq2n"}
{"name":"Time Stop","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>Time is a constant for most, but not this chronomancer. The spell slows time for all but the caster, granting her a new turn immediately after she finishes this one. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, she gets up to four actions on the turn instead of three and can ignore up to 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Multi-Actions]{Multi-Action} penalties. Time stop can only be cast once per round.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"8","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A glowing hourglass, floating ice particles, blurring.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6gccwi3q2h","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"ZTcpcrhmqNjhfxmn"}
{"name":"Message","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Message </em>can allow the wizard to deliver a message of up to twenty-five words, or fifty words with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, to a creature in which the wizard is familiar with. The recipient recognizes the sender if it knowns them, and can answer the message in a like manner.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>More Words (+1/+2):</strong> The caster can increase the number of words within the message doubling them from 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} or quadrupling them for 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Sending (+2):</strong> For 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the message can be sent across any distance and even to other planes of existance.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Unknown Recipient (+2):</strong>&nbsp;For 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the caster can send a message to a recipient that he is not familiar with provided the caster knows something that can identify the recipient.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2 miles","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whispered message to an animal, message delivered on the wind.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"aeXD2HsOOZgSkfHR"}
{"name":"Wall Walker","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Wall walker </em>allows the recepient to walk on vertical or horizontal surfaces. With @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{success}, she moves at half her normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace}. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, she may move at full @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} and even @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{run}.</p>\n<p>If forced to make an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} roll to climb or hang on to the a surface, she adds +4 to the total.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Spider-like visage, prickly hairs on hands and feet","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"bPEHSdAwCC77LChS"}
{"name":"Slumber","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>Those who favor stealth or want to avoid harming their foes are drawn to this spell, which puts its victims into a deep and restful sleep.</p>\n<p>Anyone affected by <em>slumber </em>must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if the caster got a raise on her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll). Those who fail fall asleep for the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{Duration} of the spell. Very loud noises or attempts to physically wake a sleeper (by shaking him, for example), grant another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong>&nbsp;For +2 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"A lullaby, blowing powder or sand at targets","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"bxN7J6OzYpxJQ8pV"}
{"name":"Growth/Shrink","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Growth </em>increases the recipient&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} by 1 for every 2 Power Points spent. Each increase in Size grants the target a one-step increase to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and 1 point of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness}. This does not increase @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wounds} regardless of change to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}.</p>\n<p><em>Shrink </em>reduces the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Size} of the subject one step for every 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} spent to a maximum of Size &minus;2 (approximately the size of a cat). Each step reduced decreases @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} one die type (minimum of d4) and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} by 1 (minimum of 2).</p>\n<p>For unwilling targets, the caster&rsquo;s arcane skill roll is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Duration (+2): </strong>The power&rsquo;s Duration is measured in minutes per rank instead rounds.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+2): </strong>The target of <em>shrink</em> may retain her normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Characters]{Toughness} while small.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Gestures, words of power, potions","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{},"gm-notes":{}},"_id":"cf12BmLxu6GMPY4q"}
{"name":"Augury","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p>By casting gem-inlaid sticks, rolling dragon bones, laying out ornate cards, or employing some other divining tool, you receive an omen from an otherworldly entity about the results of a specific course of action that you plan to take within the next 30 minutes, The DM chooses from the following possible omens:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>Weal</em>, for good results</li>\n<li><em>Woe</em>, for bad results</li>\n<li><em>Weal and woe</em>, for both good and bad results</li>\n<li><em>Nothing</em>, for results that aren't especially good or bad</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The spell doesn't take into account any possible circumstances that might change the outcome, such as the casting of additional spells or the loss or gain of a companion.</p>\n<p>If you cast the spell two or more times before 24 hours pass, there is a cumulative 25 percent chance for each casting after the first that you get a random reading. The DM makes this roll in secret.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Reading of cards, casting of bones.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"cgKyMDH3Mq5UaZDh"}
{"name":"Intangibility","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>With a successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll, whoever receives this power becomes incorporeal. He is unable to affect the physical world, and it cannot affect him. He can travel through walls, and non-magical weapons pass straight through him. Any items carried at the time of casting are also incorporeal.</p>\n<p>While incorporeal, the character may affect other incorporeal beings (including himself), and he is still susceptible to supernatural attacks, including powers and enchanted items. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} on the activation roll, reduce the damage from supernatural attacks by 4.</p>\n<p>The being becomes corporeal when the power ends, but if within someone or something he&rsquo;s shunted to the nearest open space and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Stunned]{stunned}.</p>\n<p>If cast on an unwilling target, the victim resists with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. If affected, he shakes off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll as a free action at the end of his following turns.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Additional Recipients (+2):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 2 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Duration (+3): </strong>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Ghost form, body of shadow, gaseous transformation","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"ciPkBrXIbIrQfGRQ"}
{"name":"Planar Travel","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Planar Travel</em> allows the caster to open a gateway to another plane. If successful, the gate opens to a point somewhere within 2d10 miles of the intended location. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the gateway opens exactly where the mage intends.</p>\n<p>If the caster doesn&rsquo;t know exactly where he wants to go, he can research locations within that plane to target a specific city, geographic location, etc. Failure means he arrives at a completely random location on that plane. Success puts him in the general vicinity, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} puts him closer to the desired locale. This is in addition to the accuracy of the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Extra-Dimensional Space (+1): </strong>Instead of traveling to a known plane, the recipient travels to a pocket dimension where he&rsquo;s conjured a magical shelter or similar structure with basic necessities, food, and water for up to five people. The structure remains afterward, so the mage and his companions may return to it as desired.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Transport Foe (+1): </strong>The caster sends an unwilling target to another plane or extra-dimensional space. The being resists the casting with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll, at &minus;2 if the caster made his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll with a raise. If failed, he&rsquo;s transported to another plane of the caster&rsquo;s choice for five rounds before returning (or as close as possible if the space is occupied).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"A summoning circle, an enchanted, iron casket, magical chains.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"crwEHbV2pS1SLTpG"}
{"name":"#[CF_tempEntity]","type":"weapon","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/weapon.svg","data":{"description":"","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"quantity":1,"weight":0,"price":0,"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"isVehicular":false,"mods":1,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"damage":"","range":"","rof":1,"ap":0,"minStr":"","shots":0,"currentShots":0,"ammo":"","autoReload":false},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6gccwi3q2h","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000","name":"Heroic","children":["js4lTFaQcIf1Agqy","ESnYArDbOE1L3PlY","ZTcpcrhmqNjhfxmn"],"folderPath":["temp_dbf611102tk"]}},"_id":"e7fWTYtDil6oDpxY"}
{"name":"Farsight","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Farsight </em>allows the recipient to see in detail over great distances. She can read lips or read fine print up to a mile distant.</p>\n<p>With a raise, she also halves @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{range penalties} for @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Shooting]{Shooting}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Athletics]{Athletics} (throwing), or other abilities affected by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{Range}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Farsight (+2): </strong>Allows the recipient to ignore all Range penalties, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} doubles sight range.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Invisibly marked targets, guiding winds, eagle eyes","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"eeTkgu91ZhVGT5qp"}
{"name":"Blind","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p>School:&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>Those affected by this malicious power suffer blurred vision or near-complete blindness with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} means the victim suffers a&nbsp;&minus;2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalty} to all actions requiring sight, or &minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>The victim automatically tries to shake off the effect with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action} at the end of his following turns.&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} removes 2 points of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties}, and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes the effect entirely.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3): </strong>For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}&nbsp;the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li><strong>Strong (+1): </strong>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll to shake of the effect is made at &minus;2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Bright flash of light, sand in eyes, confusion","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"emc7ir4pR6SUBlBk"}
{"name":"Mind Link","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p><em>Mind link </em>creates a telepathic connection between two individuals (which does not necessarily have to include the caster). The link accommodates only willing subjects and communication&mdash;thoughts that aren&rsquo;t consciously transmitted aren&rsquo;t relayed.</p>\n<p>Once @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{activated}, the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}&nbsp;between all linked minds is one mile, or five with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>If any of the linked characters suffers a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}, all others must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll or be @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken}&nbsp;(this cannot cause a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound}).</p>\n<p>The speed of communication is that of normal speech, but with a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}&nbsp;members may communicate up to 30 seconds or so of speech on a single combat turn.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Broadcast (+2): </strong>The caster can broadcast a short telepathic message to every sentient mind within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;4 radius (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;8 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). The caster can only broadcast, she doesn&rsquo;t receive their responses.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Long Distance Link (+3): </strong>Casters can connect with any mind they're familiar with on the same plane of existence, regardless of distance.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"30 minutes","trapping":"Headpieces, talismans, of Tao or other gods, crystals","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"gL5cOmzAyRBoe7VQ"}
{"name":"Leaping","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>The target of this spell can @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{jump} greater distances than normal. A success doubles his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{jumping} distances, while a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} quadruples them. Modifiers are applied after running starts are factored in.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong>&nbsp;The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Powerful legs, legs change to an animal's.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"gNtAUIVwBIEDPjCM"}
{"name":"Confusion","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p><em>Confusion </em>confounds all targets in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Medium Blast Template}, making them either @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted or Vulnerable}, or both with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The same effect applies to all those affected. These states are removed at the end of the victims&rsquo; next turn as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+0/+1):</strong>The caster can focus the <em>confusion </em>to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} for no extra cost, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +1.</li>\n<li><strong>★ Greater Confusion (+2):</strong> On a success, targets are @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} in addition to being @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} (or both with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). <em>Confusion </em>is a non-damaging effect and cannot cause a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} on an already @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Shaken} target.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Hypnotic lights, brief illusions, loud noises.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"guCMdpG90AtKtL5L"}
{"name":"Shape Change","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p>Many cultures have legends of shamans or wizards who take on the shape of animals. This power does just that, allowing the caster to take the form of any animal (including fantastic creatures such as dragons and hippogriffs, but not humanoids, undead, etc).</p>\n<p>What a character can change into depends on his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Advancement]{Rank}:</p>\n<table class=\"table value-table\"><caption class=\"table-caption\">\n<h2 class=\"table-title\">Shape Change</h2>\n</caption>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"table-header-row\">\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Cost</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Rank</th>\n<th class=\"table-column-header\" scope=\"col\">Size</th>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>Novice</td>\n<td>Size &minus;4 to Size &minus;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>Seasoned</td>\n<td>Size 0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>Veteran</td>\n<td>Size 1 to 2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11</td>\n<td>Heroic</td>\n<td>Size 3 to 4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15</td>\n<td>Legendary</td>\n<td>Size 5 to 10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>With a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}&nbsp;on the roll, the character transforms into a&nbsp; particularly large version of its type&mdash;increase its @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} and @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} by one die type each.</p>\n<p>Weapons and other personal effects are assumed into the animal&rsquo;s form and reappear when the power ends, but other objects are dropped.</p>\n<p>While transformed, the character retains his own&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hindrances]{Hindrances}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Edges]{Edges}, and linked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills} (though he may not be able to use some or all of them depending on the form -- GM&rsquo;s call). He gains the animal&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Agility}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor}, and linked @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skills} and cannot use devices that require humanoid form. He has no capacity for speech and cannot activate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{powers}, though he may continue to maintain powers previously active.</p>\n<p>A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bestiary]{creature&rsquo;s} natural abilities inherent to its form are conferred, but magical ones aren&rsquo;t. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-bestiary.Dragon]{dragon}&nbsp;can fly and breathe fire in a traditional fantasy setting, for example, so a character who <em>shape changes </em>into one may do so as well. If dragons also cast spells in that world, however, <em>shape change </em>would not grant that ability because it&rsquo;s not inherent to the physical form.</p>\n<p><strong>Size</strong>: The caster does not inherit extra @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wounds} when transforming into creatures of Large or Huge @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Size and Scale]{Scale}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Duration (+1):</strong> <em>Shape change's </em>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds.</li>\n<li><strong>Speech (+1):</strong> The recipient retains the power of speech (but still cannot activate @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Powers]{powers}).</li>\n<li><strong>Transform (+2/+3</strong>): The power may affect others at a Range of Touch for +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} or Smarts for +3 (the Range Modifier may increase this further). Unwilling targets resist with an opposed @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll and if transformed, may make another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll at the end of each of their turns to shake off the effect (at &ndash;2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). Otherwise, the power lasts for the normal Duration.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Self","duration":"5","trapping":"\"Morphing\", talismans, tattoos","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"gwKwAAR6R1Hresv9"}
{"name":"Object Reading","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p><em>Object reading </em>is the ability to get visions of the past from an object. With a successful casting, she gains a vague impression of whatever information she&rsquo;s looking for, from the object&rsquo;s creation forward. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} grants her more specific information.</p>\n<p>If the caster uses <em>object reading</em> on a bloody knife to investigate a murder, for example, success might tell her the wielder was a human and that the attack happened at night. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, she might get a glimpse of the killer&rsquo;s face or some other clue that to reveal his identity.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Projection (+2):</strong> The caster may broadcast the vision, projecting it out into a space the size of a small room. Anyone present may see and hear the events and examine the projection from all angles.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","trapping":"Touching the object, glowing hands","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"iPDPCyxeXCwV2dea"}
{"name":"Burst","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Burst </em>produces a large fan of energy that bathes its targets in red-hot fire, a cone of cold, or other damaging matter or energy.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Success} creates a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} or Steam Tempalte starting at the caster and extending outward. Everything within suffers 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage} (or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Damage (+2):</strong> The <em>burst</em> causes 3d6 damage, or 4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Burst (+4):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<em>burst</em>&nbsp;causes 4d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"2d6","range":"Cone Template","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A shower of flames, light or other matter of energy.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"j9CnJazcTatpbGt6"}
{"name":"Wish","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Universal}</p>\n<p>Wish allows a character to bend reality to his will. It is taxing to alter reality, however, so the caster must permanently sacrifice 3 of his own Power Points (after the spell is cast). A raise on the arcane skill roll eliminates this cost.</p>\n<p>A caster may wish for any one of the following effects per casting, chosen before the roll is made:</p>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Activate a Power:</strong> Wish casts any other available power, including modifiers, available in the campaign with a raise. If the spell is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed}, the target rolls with a &minus;2 penalty on top of any other modifiers. If the Power Points required to activate the power and modifiers are greater than the cost of wish, the caster must pay the difference.</li>\n<li><strong>Intercession:</strong> The caster wishes for some form of aid, which typically appears after a short period of time. A party trapped in a collapsed dungeon might wish for escape only to be rescued by a party of dwarven miners. A spellcaster could wish to know the true name of a powerful demon and be contacted the next day by a traitorous subordinate of the creature.</li>\n<li><strong>Gain an Edge:</strong> The caster can gain (or grant another) a permanent Edge. The recipient must meet the Edge&rsquo;s Requirements and can never gain more than one Edge from a wish.</li>\n<li><strong>Wealth:</strong> The spellcaster wishes for up to 10,000 gp worth of goods, including anything from transportation to supplies to magic items. Such goods generally sell for a quarter of their value. The wealth doesn&rsquo;t appear from nothing but rather comes to the caster via events contrived by the GM.</li>\n<li><strong>Travel Back Through Time:</strong> The caster travels back in time for a short period: one minute outside of combat or back to the start of the current round in combat. Everything that happened in that period is reversed except for the caster's Power Points, Bennies, and Wounds.\n<p>The GM should do her best to remember all other actors' state of things from the start of the round, but warping time is imperfect so don't worry about getting everything exactly right.</p>\n<p>Once reversed, only the caster remembers the alternate sequence of events, and that period of time cannot be altered again.</p>\n</li>\n<li><strong>See the Future:</strong> The caster peers into the near or far future. A look into the near future grants her three Conviction tokens that must be used by the caster or anyone she's currently in contact with (mental, verbal, in sight, etc.) within the next five rounds. At the end of the fifth round, any remaining tokens are discarded. A look into the far future allows the caster to ask the Game Master one question about the future and receive as accurate an answer as possible. Actions by the spellcaster can change the future, however, so this may only be the most likely path or a warning of future dangers.</li>\n<li><strong>Raise a Trait:</strong> Wish can permanently increase a Trait one die type. This increases the Trait&rsquo;s limit by one die type as well. A recipient may never have more than one Trait raised by a wish.</li>\n<li><strong>Restore Fate:</strong> The hero and all Wild Cards in Range may refill their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Bennies]{Bennies} to their usual starting maximum.</li>\n<li><strong>Special:</strong> The character may change relatively minor aspects of herself, others, or the world around her (if the subject of the wish doesn&rsquo;t want to be affected, it&rsquo;s resisted with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll at &minus;2). This shouldn&rsquo;t cause any far-reaching changes to the world or history, shouldn&rsquo;t be covered by one of the abilities above, and is completely at the whim of the Game Master. A caster can change her gender, ancestry, languages, etc., but these changes do not alter time and are thus not retroactive.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Wish can improve someone&rsquo;s mood (and their attitude on the Reaction Table, if appropriate), but it can&rsquo;t permanently affect free will. It can&rsquo;t force a change of heart or make someone harm themselves.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Legnedary","pp":"20","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A jinn from a bottle, clicked heels, an incantation, a monkey’s paw.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_pobza08y0bl","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Legendary","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"jD2W1K63wNdfRpCN"}
{"name":"Animate War Tree","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>War trees are semi-sentient, animated trees, created usually only in desperate times of need.</p>\n<p>With a success, the hero awakens one tree (which must be taller than 30') he is touching as a war tree. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the animated tree is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Wild Cards and Extras]{Wild Card}. At the end of the spell's duration, the war tree transforms back into a regular tree. If the war tree is killed before this time, the spell is automatically ended.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Hellfrost Player Guide</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Heroic","pp":"10","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Tree becomes covered in runes, warps into a \"tree man.\"","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_6gccwi3q2h","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Heroic","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"js4lTFaQcIf1Agqy"}
{"name":"Invisibility","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p>With a success, the character and his personal items are transparent except for a vague blur or outline. Any action taken against him that requires sight is made at &minus;4, or &minus;6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. The same penalty applies to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls to detect the unseen presence.</p>\n<p>Reduce the penalty by 2 if the invisible character&rsquo;s position is given away, such as moving in water, hit with mud or another substance that reveals her form, outside in the rain, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Duration (+2): </strong>Duration is measured in minutes instead of rounds. If the character attempts a damage-causing attack or targets a willing character with a power, the effect terminates immediately.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Powder, potion, iridescent lights","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"lHkhPiDJNvbbE22d"}
{"name":"Conjure Item","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p>The caster can create an object weighing up to one pound for every 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} spent. The item must be a simple, mundane object made of a common material (GM&rsquo;s call) such as a 10-foot pole, blanket, shield, etc. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll produces an more durable version of the conjured item.</p>\n<p>Conjured items appear in the hands of the caster or on the ground nearby. Once the Duration expires, the item fades from reality. This can cause issues, for example, if the conjured item holds a door open or was given as a gift.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Complexity (+2):&nbsp;</strong>The item conjured cab have modest artistry and modest complex moving parts.</li>\n<li><strong>Complete (+1): </strong>The object is a complete set, such as a chess set or a quiver of arrows. The set must fit under the weight limit.</li>\n<li><strong>Create Food and Water (Special):</strong> Instead of an object, every 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} creates enough food and water to sustain a Size 0 humanoid for one day. The nourishing food is permanent (doesn&rsquo;t disappear after you eat it), although it decays and becomes inedible after 24 hours if not consumed. The water is just like clean rainwater and does not spoil.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Creation (+4): </strong>For +4 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points}, the object created can have the volume of 1 cubic foot per 2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} spent rather than one pound.</li>\n<li><strong>Durable (+1 per pound):</strong> The object&rsquo;s Duration becomes &ldquo;permanent&rdquo; until dispelled. The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} are &ldquo;invested&rdquo; and unavailable until it&rsquo;s destroyed, dispelled, or dismissed by the caster. The conjurer may dismiss the object at any time, regardless of sight, distance, or other factors. His Power Points then begin recharging normally.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"Special","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"One hour","trapping":"Light that forms the item’s silhouette, reaching into a magic bag, shaping dirt or clay into the item, pulling the item from a drawing or painting.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"mWGtrCROcSlkCOjD"}
{"name":"Speak Language","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p>This power allows a character to speak, read, and write a sapient language other than his own. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll allows the user to appropriately use and understand slang and dialect as well.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Beasts (+1):</strong> Allows the caster the speak and understand any animal or vermin. The knowledge and awareness is limited by their intelligence.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Speak Language (+2):</strong> The caster can speak, read, and write all sapient languages at once.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Plants (+2):</strong> Allows the caster to speak and understand any plant. The sentientence of plants would limit the kinds of information they can convey.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Mass Understanding (+5):</strong> The caster causes characters within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} &times;2 of him to understand one another, regardless of language.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"10 minutes","trapping":"Words, pictures, hand motions","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"mt1r3PIWzSXs8Hpi"}
{"name":"Burrow","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Burrow</em> allows the recipient to meld into raw earth. He can remain underground if he wants in a sort of \"limbo\" or&nbsp;<em>burrow</em> through the ground at half his normal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Movement]{Pace} (or full Pace with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). He may not run.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A&nbsp;<em>burrowing </em>character may attempt to suprise a foe by making an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Stealth]{Stealth} versus @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} roll. If the burrower wins, the target is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Vulnerable} to <em>him only</em>. With a raise, the burrower gets @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.The Drop]{The Drop}. Targets on @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Hold]{Hold} may attempt to interrupt the attack before it occurs.</p>\n<p>Burrowers can't usually @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Surprise]{surprise} a foe once their presence is known, but can still burrow for protection and mobility.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n<li><strong>Power (+1):</strong> The caster can <em>burrow</em> through stone, concrete, or similar substances. (Some substances, like plastic, glass, solid lead, etc., might be resistant at the GM's discreation.)</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Dissolving into the earth and appearing elsewhere.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"o5HDyKmYQ5Mq6uwf"}
{"name":"Sound/Silence","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Illusion}</p>\n<p><em>Sound </em>mimics any known sound or voice, emanating from a point of origin within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} at a volume up to the sound of a loud shout. If used as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test}, the defender @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposes} the casting roll with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts}.</p>\n<p><em>Silence </em>does the opposite, muting all sound up to a loud shout within a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}. This subtracts 4 from @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls made by those inside the area of effect, as well as anyone trying to hear sounds made from within. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} completely mutes all sound inside the template&mdash;such @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Notice]{Notice} rolls automatically fail.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Greater Sound/Silence</strong><strong> (+1):</strong> The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll made to resist a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Test]{Test} (or Targeted modifier) is made at &minus;2.</li>\n<li><strong>Mobile (+1):</strong> The caster can move the area of effect up to his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} die type each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{round}.</li>\n<li><strong>Targeted (+0):</strong> Instead of casting <em>silence </em>in an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{area of effect}, the caster may instead target individuals in @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range} for 1 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each. Unwilling targets resist with @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} (at &minus;2 if the caster gets a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts ×5 (sound); Smarts (silence)","duration":"Instant (sound); 5 (silence)","trapping":"Magical effects, a brief ripple in the air, a bell or chime that starts or stops ringing","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"osxRMITTAHHsQn5j"}
{"name":"Consecrate/Desecrate Ground","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p>Significant or important places might become permanently &ldquo;sanctified\" or \"defiled\". Such locales are the result of long-term affiliation with a religion or belief. They usually coincide with a structure of great ceremonial significance, such as a temple, but might also arise from the scene of some great sacrifice, triumph, or tragedy.</p>\n<p>A cleric can replicate these effects on a temporary basis by strenuous prayer and devotion. The process takes four straight hours of meditation and rituals appropriate to his religion or beliefs.</p>\n<p>Once that&rsquo;s complete, the cleric makes his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} roll. Failure simply means the time is wasted. A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure} means the powers that be will not sanctify this particular place and the ritual can&rsquo;t be attempted at this location until some significant evil is defeated (DM's call).</p>\n<p>Success means an area roughly 30 yards square is anathema to the forces of darkness (or light). Any supernaturally evil (or good) creature (DM&rsquo;s call) that attempts to enter the sacred ground must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll at the start of each round (as a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{free action}) or suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue}, at &minus;2 with a raise on the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Faith]{Faith} roll. This can lead to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation}&nbsp; but not death.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong>&nbsp;@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Weird West</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"10","damage":"","range":"Special","duration":"Until the next sunset","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"owxSMTWZDKq8NWq5"}
{"name":"Sanctuary","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p>Any evil creature attempting a damaging attack that targets or affects the recipient must make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll (at &minus;2 if cast with a raise). If the roll fails, the creature loses that action.</p>\n<p>If the caster (or any allies affected by the Area Effect modifier) attempt to harm anyone (evil or otherwise), <em>sanctuary </em>terminates instantly.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+2/+3):</strong> For +2 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Points} the power affects everyone in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. For +3 points the area of effect is increased to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Strong (+1):</strong> @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} rolls by the creature are made at &minus;2 (&minus;4 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"5","trapping":"Words of power, holy symbol, glowing light","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"p1fkWcl8RV3ZarsV"}
{"name":"Bolt","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Bolt</em>&nbsp;sends damaging bursts of energy, streaks of holy light, or shards of matter toward one&rsquo;s foes.</p>\n<p>There are no @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{Range} penalties, but the&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{arcane skill roll} is affected by @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Cover and Obstacles]{Cover}, @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Illumination]{Illumination}, and all other usual @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{penalties}.</p>\n<p>The @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} of the <em>bolt </em>is 2d6, or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Damage (+2):</strong> The <em>bolt</em> causes 3d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} (4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Disintegrate (+2):</strong> If the <em>bolt </em>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitates} a creature, it immediately dies and its body disintegrates. If the target is an object, everything in a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Blast Templates]{Small Blast Template} disintegrates.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Bolt (+4):</strong> The <em>bolt</em> causes 4d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Rate of Fire (+2):</strong> The <em>bolt </em>attack is made at @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Rate of Fire]{Rate of Fire} 2.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"2d6","range":"Smarts x 2","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Fire, ice, light, darkness, colored bolts, a stream of insects","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"pccjS0dVkkL69eva"}
{"name":"Repair","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Repair </em>allows an artificer to repair damage done to complex machines and objects&mdash;essentially any device that has @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds}, like @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Vehicles]{vehicles} or certain types of constructs and living constructs. This can be any object or machine that has taken damage but are not entirely destroyed.</p>\n<p>Fixing a device or constructs @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wounds} is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll. A success repairs one @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} repairs two. If the casting fails or does not heal all the damage, the artificer may try again in an hour. On a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, the damage can only be repaired through normal hard work and replacement parts.</p>\n<p>For Extras or objects, the DM must first determine if the construct or object is already destroyed. If so, no <em>repair </em>may be attempted. If not, a successful @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll repairs the construct or object.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Deadlands Weird West</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Repair (+10):</strong> <em>Greater repairing</em> can actually rebuild objects that are completely broken as long as all parts are still available. This spell may also be used to restore constructs (but not living constructs) that have perished.</li>\n<li><strong>Repair Crippling Injuries (+10): </strong>For Living Constructs, the power can repair a permanent @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Crippling Injury} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitation} in the Savage Worlds core rules). This requires an hour of preparation and only one casting is permitted per injury. If it fails, this caster cannot heal that particular injury (but someone else may try). If successful, the subject is Exhausted for 24 hours.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Laying on of hands, working on object with a toolset.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"r4vGRk5UnKMTY0Gq"}
{"name":"Havoc","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p>This ability creates chaos and mischief for all those within its area of effect, hurling debris and rivals in all directions.</p>\n<p>With success, the caster places a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template} anywhere within @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{range}, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} emanating from the caster.</p>\n<p>Anyone touched by the template is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Distracted and Vulnerable]{Distracted} and must <em>then </em>make a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} roll (at &ndash;2 if the caster got a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}). Those who fail are hurled [[/r 2d6]]&Prime;&mdash;directly away from the caster if using the @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Cone Template} or directly away from the center if using a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Blast Template} (the caster chooses for those in the dead center).</p>\n<p>Victims who strike a hard object (such as a wall) take [[/r 2d4]] damage (@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Nonlethal Damage]{nonlethal} unless it&rsquo;s a spiked wall or other more dangerous hazard).</p>\n<p><strong>Airborne Targets</strong>: Flying or airborne targets suffer an additional &minus;2 to their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} rolls as they have no ground to brace themselves on.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+1):</strong> <em>Havoc </em>affects a&nbsp;@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Havoc (+2):</strong> Targets are knocked back a total of 3d6\" and take 2d6 damage if they strike a hard object.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Whirlwind, chaotic poltergeists, repulsion field","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"rWdCbXFw7BRV0RIw"}
{"name":"Barrier","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Barrier </em>creates a straight wall 5&Prime; (10 yards) long and 1&Prime; (two yards) tall, of immobile material that conforms to the surface it&rsquo;s cast upon. Double the length with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}.</p>\n<p>Thickness varies depending on what the wall is made of, but is usually a few inches.</p>\n<p>The wall is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 8, and may be destroyed as any other object (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Breaking Things}). Each @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Wound} destroys a 1\" (2 yard) square section of wall (piercing weapons can't damage the barrier).</p>\n<p>When the spell expires or the wall is broken it crumbles to dust or dissipates. @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trappings]{Trappings} are never left behind.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Bridge (+1): </strong>The&nbsp;<em>barrier&nbsp;</em>can be shaped to be flat and act as a bridge or roof.</li>\n<li><strong>Damage (+1): </strong>The <em>barrier </em>causes 2d4 damage to anyone who contacts it.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Deadly (+2): </strong>The <em>barrier </em>causes 2d6 damage.</li>\n<li><strong>Tough (+1): </strong>The wall is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Breaking Things]{Hardness} 10.</li>\n<li><strong>Shaped (+1): </strong>The <em>barrier </em>forms a circle, square, or rectangle. It can't have a roof or floor, and can't Bind or Entangle anything within (use the @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Entangle]{entangle} power for that).</li>\n<li><strong>Size (+1): </strong>The length and height of the <em>barrier </em>doubles.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Fire, ice, thorns, force, bones, energy.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"s7t1gwhTMqHwaPPc"}
{"name":"Magic Mark","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Magic mark </em>can be visible or invisible. If a <em>magic mark </em>was created as a visible mark, a caster can use <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{conceal arcana}</em><em>&nbsp;</em>to temporarily hide it. Casting <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Detect/Conceal Arcana]{detect </em><em>arcana} </em>will reveal a permanent or temporarily concealed <em>magic mark</em>. Casting @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-powers.Dispel]{dispel} on an <em>magic mark </em>can remove it permanently.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Eberron</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Permenant","trapping":"Mystical tattoos, invisible sigils, arcane runes.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"t0xFjlGgWm9kLGYS"}
{"name":"Analyze Foe","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School: </strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Divination}</p>\n<p>Knowledge is power. Being able to judge the strength of a foe before engaging him in combat can be highly advantageous.</p>\n<p>The character makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the target's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. On a success, he gains a +1 bonus to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls to directly affect the target, and the target suffers a &minus;1 penalty to @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Trait} rolls to directly affect the caster. With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the effect is increased to +2 and &minus;2 for both.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Fantasy Companion</strong></em></p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Information (+2): </strong>A success allows the caster to learn of a single @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Immunity]{Immunity}, @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Invulnerability]{Invulnerability}, or @Compendium[savage-eberron-bestiary.savage-eberron-bestiary-abilities.Weakness]{Weakness} of the target (if one exists), and a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} allows the knowledge of two.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"1","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"Mystical sense, spiritual advice, gestalt knowledge","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"tt7BzDHMPPCXvPLV"}
{"name":"Planar Binding","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Conjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Planar binding</em> allows a caster to summon and contain a creature from another plane to a trap of some sort, such as a binding circle, pentagram, mystic circle, etc. The trap is created with chalk, salt, paint, glyphs and wards, or other materials prior to the power's activation, and takes ten minutes of time to prepare.</p>\n<p>Once the trap is prepared, the summoner states what type of extra-planar creature she wishes to bind. She must know about the creature somehow, perhaps by previous encounter, access to strange books and scrolls, or an Occult roll with a bonus or penalty set by the Game Master depending on the creature. The summoner can even summon a specific entity if she knows its proper name.</p>\n<p>Casting is an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} between the summoner's arcane skill and the entity's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. If the entity wins, the spell fails and the entity knows who attempted to bind it. If the caster rolls a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{Critical Failure}, the creature may appear if it chooses to and is unbound&mdash; it may do as it wishes and its abilities allow.</p>\n<p>If the caster wins, the creature is summoned into the trap and magically bound there until it agrees to perform a service for the caster or breaks free (see below). The Power Points used to bind the target are invested and unavailable until the creature breaks free or is released.</p>\n<p>The summoner may free the entity as a free action anytime she chooses, regardless of sight, distance, or other factors. When she does so, she decides if it remains on her plane or returns to whichever plane it was summoned from.</p>\n<p><strong>Bargaining:</strong> Casters summon creatures to task them with a \"service\" of some sort, such as taking part in a difficult battle, acting as a bodyguard, or performing some task the caster can't or doesn't want to perform herself. The negotiation can usually be handled through roleplaying (and perhaps a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Persuasion]{Persuasion} or @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-skills.Intimidation]{Intimidation} roll).</p>\n<p>Cunning creatures require more incentive. An evil being might ask for time to wander the earth and wreak havoc, a sacrifice, or some other \"devil's bargain\" proportional to the service required. A good or noble creature might aid the summoner without reward if the cause is just, or might require she perform some task for her followers or sphere of influence. Entities never agree to services they can't perform or that will clearly result in their destruction.</p>\n<p>Once the creature agrees to the terms, it must carry them out to the best of its ability. The caster does not have to live up to any promises she set&mdash;though entities might seek revenge if deceived or their kind are summoned too often. Casters must be wary of this, especially if the beings have a way back to the prime material plane!</p>\n<p><strong>Breaking Free:</strong> If no agreement is made after 24 hours, the caster must renew the mystic bonds by making another @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed roll} of her @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} versus the creature's @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit}. This continues every 24 hours until an agreement is reached or the creature breaks free. The entity can't use any other power or ability to escape.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<p><em><strong>Source: Savage Pathfinder</strong></em></p>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"8","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A summoning circle, an enchanted, iron casket, magical chains.","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"uDyxykyoTcArW9Pj"}
{"name":"Mind Wipe","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Enchantment}</p>\n<p><em>Mind wipe </em>removes a target&rsquo;s memories, a terrible violation in most civilized societies. The power is @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by a victim&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} and requires a full minute of mental struggle. The victim must be conscious during this time, so if not restrained he can simply move out of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Range]{Range}.</p>\n<p>If @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{successful}, the victim forgets a single event (up to about 30 minutes of time). A @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} removes a complex memory of several hours.</p>\n<p>If the defender wins, the caster cannot affect him with <em>mind wipe </em>for 24 hours. (Others may reattempt the power, however.)</p>\n<p>The memory remains missing but strong evidence that challenges its &ldquo;logic&rdquo; allows a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} roll at &minus;2 to remember fragments determined by the GM.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Edit (+1):</strong> Instead of wiping the memory, the caster edits it as she sees fit.</li>\n<li><strong>Fast Cast (+2):</strong> The caster can wipe a memory as an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{action}.</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Mind Wipe (+2):</strong> The effect completely removes a single event, person, place, thing, etc., from the victim&rsquo;s memory.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Veteran","pp":"3","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"Instant","trapping":"A noxious drink, parasites, touching the target's temples","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_impxt7vt72","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Veteran","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"ut0XJvwWRwyj5kPL"}
{"name":"Deflection","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Abjuration}</p>\n<p><em>Deflection </em>powers work in a variety of ways. Some manifestations actually deflect incoming @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{attacks}, others blur the target&rsquo;s form or produce illusionary effects. The end result is always the same, however&mdash;to misdirect incoming melee and missile @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Attacks]{attacks}&nbsp;from the recipient of the power.</p>\n<p>With success, foes must subtract 2 from either melee or ranged attacks (caster&rsquo;s choice). With a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}, the penalty applies to both.</p>\n<p>An attacker who uses a ranged weapon in melee against the recipient suffers the penalty either way.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Additional Recipients (+1):</strong> The power may affect more than one target for 1 additional @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{Power Point} each.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Novice","pp":"2","damage":"","range":"Smarts","duration":"5","trapping":"Mystical shield, gust of wind, phantom servant that intercepts missiles","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_wcbttwzemz","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Novice","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"vXcUn5K9IotOjvQm"}
{"name":"Blast","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Evocation}</p>\n<p><em>Blast</em> launches a ball of explosive energy or matter. The area of effect is a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Medium Blast Template}. Every target within suffers 2d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage]{damage}, or 3d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise} (see @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Area Effect Attacks}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li><strong>Area of Effect (+0/+1):</strong> The caster can focus the blast to a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Small Blast Template} for no extra cost, or a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Area Effect Attacks]{Large Blast Template} for +1.</li>\n<li><strong>Damage (+2):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<em>blast</em>&nbsp;causes 3d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage} (4d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Greater Blast (+4):</strong>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<em>blast</em> causes 4d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} (5d6 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}).</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"3","damage":"2d6","range":"Smarts x 2","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Balls of fire, ice, light, darkness, colored bolts, swarm of insects","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"wRSuntiUWRvIFJgf"}
{"name":"Telekinesis","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Transmutation}</p>\n<p><em>Telekinesis </em>is the ability to move objects or creatures (including oneself) with arcane will. It has a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Strength} of d10, or d12 with a raise.</p>\n<p>Unwilling opponents resist the caster&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} with an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll when targeted and at the start of each of their @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Actions]{turns} afterward until they&rsquo;re released. They can be moved up to the caster&rsquo; @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Smarts} per turn in any direction, and can be bashed into walls, ceilings, or other obstacles for Str+d6 @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{damage}.</p>\n<p>Dropped creatures suffer @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Falling]{falling damage} as usual.</p>\n<p><strong>Telekinetic Tools</strong>: A caster can wield tools (including weapons) with <em>telekinesis </em>as an action. Use the caster&rsquo;s relevant @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{skill} when attacking in this way (not his @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill}).</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Power (+3): </strong>The Strength of telekinesis is d12, or d12 + 2 with a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{raise}. Objects weighing 1,000 pounds or more automatically deal @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Heavy Weapon (HW)]{Heavy} @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Dealing Damage]{Damage} when used as weapons.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Smarts x2","duration":"5","trapping":"A wave of the hand, magic wand, steely gaze","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"},"journal-links":{}},"_id":"xwN8a3oshjcTDZIw"}
{"name":"Curse","type":"power","img":"systems/swade/assets/icons/power.svg","data":{"description":"<div class=\"swade-core savage-eberron-core\">\n<p><strong>School:&nbsp;</strong>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Schools of Magic]{Necromancy}</p>\n<p>Some practitioners of the arcane arts heal their allies. Others inflict sickness upon their enemies. To use this particularly nasty spell, the caster makes an @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Arcane Backgrounds]{arcane skill} roll @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Trait Rolls]{opposed} by the victim&rsquo;s @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Spirit} roll. Failure means the victim suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} immediately and at sunset each day thereafter (further castings of <em>curse</em> have no additional effect).</p>\n<p>Once the accursed becomes @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, he makes a @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Traits]{Vigor} roll each day to avoid death.</p>\n<p><strong>Breaking the Curse:</strong> The <em>curse</em> can be lifted by the original caster at will, and ends automatically if she&rsquo;s slain. <em>@Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-powers.Dispel]{Dispel}</em> also removes a <em>curse</em> (at &minus;2), though each individual may only try once&mdash;if failed it&rsquo;s beyond her abilities.</p>\n<p><strong>Helpful Links:</strong> @Compendium[savage-eberron-rules.savage-eberron-rules.Using Magic]{Using Magic} - @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Power Modifiers}</p>\n<h3>@Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Power Modifiers]{Modifiers}</h3>\n<ul class=\"red-bullet-list\">\n<li class=\"star\"><strong>Turn to Stone (+5): </strong>The accursed suffers a level of @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Fatigue]{Fatigue} each round instead of each day. When @Compendium[swade-core-rules.swade-rules.Damage Effects]{Incapacitated}, the victim turns to stone and is considered an object.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","notes":"","additionalStats":{},"equippable":false,"equipped":false,"actions":{"skill":"","skillMod":"","dmgMod":"","additional":{}},"rank":"Seasoned","pp":"5","damage":"","range":"Touch","duration":"Instant","trapping":"Effigy, ritualistic words, vile curse spoken","arcane":"","skill":"","modifiers":[]},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"DX8acFfCTTwwzgWq":3},"flags":{"journal-links":{},"cf":{"id":"temp_ds3hec49ph","path":"Powers#/CF_SEP/Seasoned","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"zS1IHXdyG85Zr2e6"}
